Slice sequences

{% raw %} 
a = ['a', 'b', 'c', 'd', 'e', 'f', 'g', 'h']
print('Middle two: ', a[3:5])
print('All but end: ', a[:-1])

Middle two:  ['d', 'e']
All but end:  ['a', 'b', 'c', 'd', 'e', 'f', 'g']
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
assert a[:5] == a[0:5] # Should leave out zero index
assert a[5:] == a[5:len(a)] # Should leave out the final index
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
first_twenty_items = a[:20]
first_twenty_items, len(first_twenty_items)

(['a', 'b', 'c', 'd', 'e', 'f', 'g', 'h'], 8)
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
last_twenty_items = a[-20:]
last_twenty_items, len(last_twenty_items)
# But direct index will show error
# a[20] # IndexError: list index out of range

(['a', 'b', 'c', 'd', 'e', 'f', 'g', 'h'], 8)
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
b = a[3:]
print('b', b)
print('a', a)
b[1] = 100
print('b', b)
print('a', a)

b ['d', 'e', 'f', 'g', 'h']
a ['a', 'b', 'c', 'd', 'e', 'f', 'g', 'h']
b ['d', 100, 'f', 'g', 'h']
a ['a', 'b', 'c', 'd', 'e', 'f', 'g', 'h']
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
b = a[:]
assert b == a
assert b is not a
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
a1 = a
a2 = a[:]
assert a1 == a and a2 == a
id(a), id(a1), id(a2)

(139689729223168, 139689729223168, 139689728128336)
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
assert a1 is a
assert a2 is not a
{% endraw %} {% raw %}

a = [100,103, 105]

print('a', a)

b ['a', 'b', 'c', 'd', 'e', 'f', 'g', 'h']
a ['a', 'b', 'c', 'd', 'e', 'f', 'g', 'h']
b ['a', 'b', 'c', 'd', 'e', 'f', 'g', 'h']
a [100, 103, 105]
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
b = a
print('b', b)
print('a', a)
a[:] = ['a','b']
print('b', b)
print('a', a)

b [100, 103, 105]
a [100, 103, 105]
b ['a', 'b']
a ['a', 'b']
